The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for classification and generative tasks, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on the improvement of training results by adding supplementary information to disentangle data representation, which is a common technique in deep learning research and falls under the scope of these sub-categories.
